message.entry: The first input argument must be a vector.
The second input argument must be a character array or string representing a MATLAB data type, such as ''double''.
The first input must contain a multiple of {0,number,integer} elements to convert from {1} ({2,number,integer} bits) to {3} ({4,number,integer} bits).
The first input argument must be a full, non-complex numeric value.
